- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Subscription/SubscriptionToken.cs
    Pure C# implementation of ISubscriptionToken (Abstractions).
    Public sealed class with an internal constructor that accepts the
    unregister callback supplied by the registry. Dispose semantics:
        - First Dispose call wins atomically via Interlocked.Exchange
          and runs the unregister callback exactly once.
        - Subsequent Dispose calls are observable no-ops (no second
          unregister, no exception, IsDisposed remains true).
        - The callback reference is cleared after invocation so that
          captured closures become eligible for GC even if the token
          itself is held longer.
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Subscription/SubscriptionToken.cs.meta
- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Subscription/TopicSubscriptionRegistry.cs
    Pure C# topic × kind subscription registry. Implements
    IDispatchHandlerLookup so MainThreadDispatchQueue can use it as
    its handler lookup directly. Public API:
        - Register(topic, kind, handler, payloadType?) →
          ISubscriptionToken. Adds a Registration (handler delegate
          + optional payload Type metadata for future typed-bus
          wrapping in task 2.5) to the (topic, kind) bucket. Returns
          a SubscriptionToken whose Dispose performs a constant-time
          unregister of exactly that Registration instance — even if
          the same delegate has been registered multiple times.
        - TryGetHandlers(topic, kind, out handlers) — Returns a
          DispatchHandler[] snapshot of the bucket so that mid-
          dispatch Dispose calls do not mutate the array
          MainThreadDispatchQueue is iterating. Snapshot order
          matches registration order, so handlers fire in a
          deterministic order under Flush.
        - CountFor(topic, kind) — registration count for a single
          key, used by the test suite to assert idempotent Dispose
          and concurrent registration visibility.
        - RegistrationCount / RegisteredKeyCount — totals across
          all buckets, exposed for diagnostics and tests.
    Concurrency model:
        - All Dictionary mutations and snapshot construction occur
          inside a single private lock. This is simpler than a
          copy-on-write array per (topic, kind) and is more than
          fast enough for subscription churn, which is rare compared
          with envelope dispatch. The hot path (TryGetHandlers from
          Flush on the main thread) takes the lock only long enough
          to copy the list.
        - Empty buckets are removed on the last unregistration so
          RegisteredKeyCount accurately reflects live keys.
