Implementation summary:
- New namespace VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Subscription inside the
  existing VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core asmdef. No asmdef change is
  required: Core already references Abstractions and the new files
  use only BCL types plus VTuberSystemBase.CoreIpc.Core.Dispatch
  (DispatchHandler / IDispatchHandlerLookup).
- ISubscriptionToken stays in the Abstractions asmdef as defined in
  ICoreIpcBus.cs (design.md §509). The concrete SubscriptionToken
  lives in Core so Abstractions remains free of implementation
  details (Req 1.6).
- Registry implements IDispatchHandlerLookup directly; this is the
  integration point design.md §613 calls for. Wiring into a real
  CoreIpcBus comes later in task 2.5.
- The optional payloadType parameter on Register is metadata only
  (matches "delegate + payload Type" in tasks.md §2.4 and the
  SubscriptionRegistration entity in design.md §972). It is stored
  on the Registration record so a future CoreIpcBus implementation
  can use it during JsonElement → TPayload deserialization without
  reshaping the registry API.
- Dispose semantics follow the "多重 Dispose は no-op" requirement
  from tasks.md §2.4: Interlocked.Exchange ensures the unregister
  callback runs exactly once even under concurrent Dispose races.
- TryGetHandlers returns a fresh DispatchHandler[] snapshot, not a
  live view of the internal List. This is what makes mid-flush
  Dispose safe: a handler invoked during Flush can dispose another
  subscription without mutating the array MainThreadDispatchQueue is
  currently iterating (the queue stores the snapshot in a local).

